<span style="color:#00a859;">Contact with these colored circles is highly recommended to be avoided in <span style="color:#00afef;">Level 142.1</span>. Although they initially look identical to those in <span style="color:#ed3237;">Level 142</span>, more extended observations reveal discrepancies in texture, temperature, and behavior. While some of them sink down under pressure as if they are pressed into a wall, others have resistance similar to that of muscle or inflamed skin. The typical reaction to contact with these circles is described as "warm paint over soft surface." </span>

<span style="color:#fff212;">Those who have touched these areas for long enough say that they can feel a very slight movement under their fingertips. The range of descriptions includes faint twitching up to a slow and rhythmic pulsing, much like a heartbeat. There have been some instances where circles would "squeeze" around the subject's hand before settling down back to normal shortly afterward. One wanderer claimed that he could press on one of the yellow circles and that it felt like "a blister giving way." It was said to burst inward and leave no mark behind, only revealing the inner white fibers. </span>

<span style="color:#00afef;">Most troubling spots are those involving heat exchange. Several wanderers have reported that some of these circles felt hot to the touch even though there was no rise in temperature detected using an infrared detector. Wanderers affected were observed to get temporary numbness in their hand in contact with the circles, followed by the feeling that "something is still touching them." There are no reports of anyone getting ailments from contact with the circles. Nevertheless, people who experienced such contact tend to shy away from more physical contact with painted objects. </span> 
</tabber>
==<span style="color:#ed3237;">Colonies & Outposts</span>==
<span style="color:#00afef;">There are no known colonies, camps, or other types of structures inside the <span style="color:#ed3237;">Level 142.1</span>. Efforts to create camped-out places have always resulted in failure because of the intensification of Pigment Loss effects, confusion arising from changes in room layout, and the growing mental problems caused by spending time in this area. No expeditions dedicated to mapping this sublevel have been successful. </span>
==<span style="color:#00afef;">Entities</span>==
<span style="color:#ed3237;">There are no identified entities present at <span style="color:#fff212;">Level 142.1</span>. However, it is clear from various activities of the level that it exhibits signs of being aware of its surroundings. 

The flower structures have apparently moved since previous observations; the colorful circles often respond to touch, and several audio recordings feature voices that are never heard during any firsthand experiences. 

The loss of coloration is deemed to be the biggest danger that comes with this level. It is believed that if there are entities present, they either blend in with the surroundings or become visible after some time. </span>
==<span style="color:#711c65">Entrances & Exits</span>==
===<span style="color:#00a859;">Entrances</span>===
- Licking & tasting any colorful circle in <span style="color:#00a859;">[[Level 142]]</span> will lead you here. 

